A towering ancient tree with an intricate root system visible underground, where the roots transform into glowing fiber optic cables and network connections spreading in all directions. The tree's branches above ground split into increasingly complex hierarchical patterns, with each major branch subdividing into smaller branches in a perfect organizational structure. Vintage 1990s computer terminals and servers are nestled among the roots like archaeological artifacts, some covered in moss and vines, suggesting the passage of technological eras. The scene is bathed in warm sepia and amber tones with subtle green undertones. Style: Vintage illustration with aged paper texture, muted earth tones, and fine crosshatching details reminiscent of old botanical scientific drawings from the 19th century. The overall composition suggests both organic growth and digital infrastructure merging into one unified system, conveying evolution and technological history.
